16th evening. A large letter from Hebich with Papa's home letter. No news
in it but 2all are well1. You will get it in a few days, I send it first to
M”gl who is still near. In half an hour this must be on the postoffice. I
had to write (or translate) so much for M

611... am quite tired and must beg your pardon* for not writing more just
now. Mrs Gr sends also Selam. I showed her the boys letters. Mr Hoch is a
nice open brother, with W<rth>* we go on without coming very close still
very friendly. Now grace be with you all
